## Confined establishment - ZOO Praha

## Prague Zoo - Prague Region - HPAI2-13/2026

- -11. 2. 2026 suspicion - death of 8 birds in 1 epizootic unit, The other 87 birds showed no clinical signs.
- -12.2.2026  NRL confirmation HPAI H5N1
- -The outbreak was defined as the section of the zoo - defined epizootic unit (two adjacent aviaries: pelican exhibit + Asian lagoon).
- -The epizootic unit contains genetically valuable or protected bird species. Therefore, an exemption from culling for closed facilities was applied in accordance with Article 13 (paragraphs 2 and 3) of Regulation 687/2020.
- -Weekly monitoring has been set up in this epizootic unit - laboratory testing for AI of representative number of samples + every death will be examined + clinical surveillance of the disease has been put in place.
- -The outbreak area is closed to the public and operationally separated from other parts of the zoo (designated staff).
- -In other parts of the zoo - AI testing in the event of bird deaths or clinical signs of infection + clinical surveillance introduced.
- -In addition to the aforementioned epizootological unit, the ZOO keeps 1,225 birds at 24 locations.

