## Preventive actions

## 5.12.2025 - 7.1.2026

Extraordinary veterinary measures for a defined risk area around restricted zones of outbreaks HPAI1-6/2025, HPAI1-7/2025, HPAI1-8/2025, HPAI1-9/2025, HPAI1-10/2025 ('Blatná' a 'Skály u Protivína')

The area with a total area of   12,400 km² included the territory of three regions: South Bohemia, Central Bohemia, and Pilsen.

Based on the improvement in the disease situation in the region, the measures were lifted at the same time as the last restricted zone in the area was lifted.

<!-- image -->

A map with a purple area and three highlighted areas.

<!-- image -->

## Measures ordered in the area according to national legislation

## Measures for Bird breeders

Bird breeders were ordered to prevent contact between farmed birds and wild birds to the greatest extent possible and to prevent contamination of water and feed for farmed birds with wild bird droppings.

Breeders of birds originating from the risk area were prohibited from participating in gatherings and public performances within the whole theritory of the Czech Republic.

Commercial breeders in this area had to keep records of all persons entering the farm.

<!-- image -->

## Measures for stations for handicapped animals

Operators of rescue stations for handicapped animals in the area were required to report to the competent authority the deaths of birds at the station, unless the death is demonstrably related to injury. They also had to keep records of bird deaths at the rescue station.

<!-- image -->

## Measures for feathered game hunts

Before the event, organizers of feathered game hunts had to provide evidence of a negative result for avian influenza for a specified number of birds from the flock that is to be the subject of the hunt.

The hunt had to be reported to the local RVA at least three days in advance. The movement of hunted game birds was only be possible within the Czech Republic.

<!-- image -->

## Other preventive actions

Prior to migration wild birds wave, we carried out an awareness campaign in anticipation of the autumn migration, targeting poultry keepers. We contacted all municipalities, requesting that they publish information on their official notice boards about the risks of HPAI and NCD, the approaching autumn migration, and the importance of preventive measures.

## Follow-up actions

Informing the general public through press releases, web pages SVS and the professional community through letters about the increased risk of spread situation and the importance of preventive measures.

